description: Setsuna opens up to Towa about the hidden village for half-demons where she was raised for most of her childhood.

input: The Hidden Village for Half Demons

title: The Hidden Village for Half Demons

description: On the night of the new moon, Riku pays Towa a visit to chat. Unfortunately, he's not the only one planning to drop by.
title: Secret of the Rainbow Pearls

description: Konton devises a plan to destroy the Half-Demon Princesses. Riku offers to help him out. The three girls are lured into a ravine and fall right into Konton's trap.
title: Trap of the Two Perils

description: Konton learns of the origins of the Rainbow Pearl and the connection between Kirinmaru and the Dream Butterfly. He summons an ogre to attack the Half-Demon Princesses.
title: Sesshomaru and Kirinmaru

description: The deputy shogun's daughter Aiya offers to employ the demon slayers if they win in a battle against the bounty hunters.
title: Princess Aiya's Beniyasha Hunting

description: Zero removes the seal that Miroku placed on Setsuna to suppress her demon powers, awakening the latent demon blood within.
title: The Stolen Seal

description: Setsuna and Towa hire Moroha to help slay Zero. The trio successfully track Zero down, but Riku stands in their way.
title: The Three Princesses Strike Back

description: Towa, Setsuna, and Moroha are left to confront Kirinmaru, but in the face of overwhelming power, they must pay a great price.
title: Sesshomaru's Daughter

description: A demon emerges in the present day with Setsuna, Towa's twin, and the bounty hunter Moroha in tow. Seeing Setsuna in trouble awakens Towa's latent demon powers.
title: The Dream Butterfly

description: Towa Higurashi learns about an incident that took place decades ago involving a half demon named Inuyasha and a priestess named Kagome.
title: Inuyasha: Since Then

description: Half-demon twins Towa and Setsuna are separated from each other when a mysterious tunnel sends Towa into the future, where she is found and raised by Kagome Higurashi's brother Sota.
title: The Three Princesses

description: Towa and Setsuna take on a request to slay Jakotsumaru, a boy who has been extracting bones from humans and beasts in order to revive his father, the demon beast Tokotsu.

input: Jakotsumaru of the Red Bone Palace

title: Jakotsumaru of the Red Bone Palace

description: Towa decides to return to the feudal era to help Setsuna regain her memories. The trio enter the corridor leading to the feudal era, but within it awaits the spirit of a certain priestess.
title: The Gateway to the Past

description: Travelers are going missing one after another. Towa, Setsuna, and Moroha head to the northern mountains to crack the case, but instead they find a village completely overrun by ghost cats!

input: The Cat Juan at the Old Temple
Cat Juan at the Old Temple

title: The Cat Juan at the Old Temple

description: On her way to search for the Dream Butterfly, Towa meets a strange young man named Riku. Towa offers him an apple, and in thanks, Riku presents her with the genuine Kikujumonji sword.
title: Meeting through an Apple

description: After fleeing from the deputy shogun's estate, Yotsume borrows the power of a Rainbow Pearl to unleash his Dream Gazing spell upon the Half-Demon Princesses, who are hot on his trail.
title: The Dream Gazing Trap

description: Moroha accepts a job to slay Konton, a member of the Four Perils said to have defeated Meioju, a demon beast with the ultimate armored shell.
title: Meifuku, the Meioju

description: The Half-Demon Princesses are tasked with slaying Kinka and Ginka, conjoined twins of the Ka Demon Tribe whose battles for dominance have been wreaking havoc everywhere.

input: The Gold and Silver Rainbow Pearls

title: The Gold and Silver Rainbow Pearls

description: Something wicked lurks in the Man-Eating Pond, devouring any human, beast or bird that comes near. Towa and Setsuna meet Hikomaru and Chiyo, siblings who lost their parents to the pond.
title: Curse of the Man-Eating Pond

description: The demon Nikosen was a sage before evil consumed his soul. Konton orders him to kill the Half-Demon Princesses. Towa struggles as her demon powers fade and she turns into a human.

input: Night of the New Moon and the Black-haired Towa
of the New Moon and the Black-haired Towa
the New Moon and the Black-haired Towa
New Moon and the Black-haired Towa

title: Night of the New Moon and the Black-haired Towa

description: When a demon begins to devour virtuous monks and Shinto priests in the region, Hisui is assigned to guard his father, Miroku, who has been undergoing harsh training for the past two years.
title: The Delicious Feudal Monks

description: Towa and Setsuna set off to slay Homura, an evil mountain god who has abducted a beautiful maiden. The twins learn that Homura was involved in the forest fire that separated them.

input: The One Behind the Forest Fire

title: The One Behind the Forest Fire

description: The truth behind the night that sealed the fate of Towa, Setsuna, and Moroha's parents is finally revealed.
title: Farewell Under the Lunar Eclipse

description: Moroha once had a master named Yawaragi, who was keeping a life-threatening secret. In order to resolve the secret and protect her pupil, Yawaragi made an agreement with Jyubei.
title: Double-Edged Moroha

description: Sesshomaru hands the broken Tenseiga to a grieving Towa, leaving Setsuna's fate in her hands. Will Towa be able to bring Setsuna back to life?
title: Wielding the Tenseiga

description: Towa learns about a demon that targets women with long, beautiful hair. Meanwhile, Moroha and Setsuna help a nun who isn't exactly what she seems…
title: Demon Spirit of the Sea

description: Jaken recalls that fateful day fourteen years ago when Zero placed a curse on Rin. The three girls search for Bokusen-Oh.
title: The Silver-Scale Curse

description: The three girls arrive at Mount Musubi but are trapped by a powerful barrier. Moroha manages to escape and runs into something unexpected.
title: The Barrier at Mount Musubi

description: Trapped within Mount Musubi, Rion's soul longs for peace. Rion asks Setsuna to sever the thread of fate connects her to her father, Kirinmaru.
title: The Girl Named Rion

description: Setsuna is kidnapped by Princess Aiya, daughter of the deputy shogun, who begs Setsuna to be her body double for a day so she can escape her studies.
title: Hisui the Demon Slayer

description: Takechiyo hires Moroha to help him with the familial strife at his home. Kohaku teaches Towa an important lesson about learning to run away.
title: Takechiyo's Request

description: The demon slayers struggle to put out the fires caused by the Flame Bulls. Mayonaka demands the villagers hand over the town's divine object.
title: Mayonaka the Visitor

description: Zero sets a trap in the garden of Nanahoshi, a demon who feeds on sadness. Kohaku, Hisui, and Setsuna assist the demon slayers in the north.
title: Nanahoshi's Mini Galaxy

description: Moroha learns about the Full Moon Raccoon Dog and Takechiyo's exile. The snow demon Yukinyudo attacks Setsuna. Zero targets Towa on the new moon.

input: Battle on the New Moon, Part 1

title: Battle on the New Moon, Part 1

description: Zero unearths Towa's sadness and loneliness. Sesshomaru appears before the demon slayers and commands Setsuna to pay the Tree of Ages a visit.
title: A Place (Not) for Towa

description: Moroha and Takechiyo strike back against Shogen Mamiana. Setsuna experiences her first New Moon. Towa is trapped by Nanahoshi's eternity bugs.

input: Battle on the New Moon, Part 2

title: Battle on the New Moon, Part 2

description: Setsuna stops Towa from killing Zero. Rin's curse cannot be lifted unless Zero lets go of her regrets. Sesshomaru gives Moroha the Black Pearl.
title: Zero's Wish

description: Moroha is finally reunited with her parents. Inuyasha sees a way out of the Black Pearl. Kirinmaru's attack leaves Sesshomaru gravely injured.
title: Moroha and Family, Together Again

description: Kirinmaru takes the Black Pearl from Moroha. Towa, Setsuna, and Sesshomaru arrive at the scene. Meanwhile, Rion and Riku head to Mount Musubi.
title: Kirinmaru of the Dawn

description: Kirinmaru faces off against Sesshomaru. Towa summons the Tenseiga. Shippo waits for Inuyasha and the others at Gozu and Mezu's gate.
title: The Three Princesses Escape

description: Osamu Kirin sees the Grim Comet approaching, and the Spirit of the Tree of Ages orders the half-demon princesses to go destroy it.
title: Akuru's Pinwheel

description: To destroy the Grim Comet, Towa, Moroha, and Setsuna must travel through the Windmill of Time, but Meidomaru stands in their way.

input: The Collapse of the Windmill of Time
Collapse of the Windmill of Time

title: The Collapse of the Windmill of Time
